  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The intraperitoneal repair has been proven safe for the repair of incisional hernia and is
      accepted, together with the subfascial or retromuscular repair as the &quot;gold-standard&quot; for the
      repair of incisional hernia. However no studies have convincingly proven that this approach
      is better than the on-lay repair.

      The authors believe that the intraperitoneal repair performs better than the on-lay repair
      for incisional hernia.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
